caption: A great server. Really customer minded. Helpful in taking our order. Will be back. Everyone should drop in an enjoy the food and service.
The staff is great and the food is delicious! I'll be back very soon!
Completely forgot this was here!! I will definitely be back soon!
Good food. Very enjoyable staff. Our waitress was friendly and attentive. Answered our questions about the restaurant history. We would go again.
The service was some of the best and the food was delicious. Our waitress definitely earned more than.
Dinner was excellent.  Our friend had a burger that he really enjoyed.
Finally had the chance to try out this place, Delicious Food and great service! Must visit , will recommend to my all friends. So good! So tasty!

Vinci is awesome!! The food and service were both phenomenal! The truffle gnocchi is a must and you really can’t go wrong with anything on the menu. They also have $20 bottles of wine on Thursday and Sunday’s. It is a hidden gem that I can’t recommend enough!
Great service, solid food, good enough price point. It’s hard to find a good spot in Covid times, and this is one of them! Recommended parties of 4 or less
Richard R at the bar made us feel right at home! Great food and drink recommendations.
Talk about comfort food!!! Rich, decedant and flavored to perfection. The service was always outstanding here and delivery is still just as good!
Always very solid. Consistency great food. Excellent service
One of my go-to places to grab some food. very good location, neat, and excellent customer service. Keep it up!
I really enjoyed their dishes and customer service, fantastic location very close to where I live. The employees are always kind. Will visit here again.
Good food and service

Service is phenomenal. Always a great stop before or after enjoying a show at Steppenwolf. Walking distance from the theatre plus take advantage of including your valet parking for dinner and show. Never disappointed with heartwarming Italian dishes and wine.
Love it before a Steppenwolf play, or after!
Small authentic Italian well executed and presented
Loved the food quality and taste! It also has competitive prices.
Great food, great staff.

Service is phenomenal. Always a great stop before or after enjoying a show at Steppenwolf. Walking distance from the theatre plus take advantage of including your valet parking for dinner and show. Never disappointed with heartwarming Italian dishes and wine selection.

Amazing pastas, great location, very welcoming.  I was there for a work holiday party but I'm looking forward to my next visit.  The ingredients were high quality and all food tasted amazing.  It is a little pricey but there are weekday deals that look great.  I plan on coming back for those.  The rigatoni with vodka sauce, baked chicken, and the bruschetta were all to die for.  Absolutely delicious, thanks for a great time!
Just what we wanted after a long day of shopping. Simple and effective Italian.  The service is excellent. Attentive and lively.
Food was great. The owner came over to introduce herself and explained that everything was made from her family recipies. She was very sweet and welcoming. I will be definitely going back!

Goodness, what a delight! Our accidental destination (long story), and our fabulous waiter, Miguel (from Adobo Grill, actually) was an amazing experience to celebrate the birthday of a very dear 'life friend' and an out of town guest! Our 'party of 5' couldn't have been better served or treated if we'd planned this months in advance!  From the appetizers (sausage, meatballs and arancini to match my homemade) .. to 5 dinners to share (including squid ink tagliatelle, brick chicken, succulent pork chops bone-in, to the perfectly cooked ravioli) .. great wine list .. our corner table in the window was open yet intimate and a perfect experience!
Great food and the best service!
Great food👏🏽🙏🏽👍🏽👌🏽🔥
I love the ravioli and it is a great place to eat before heading over to Steppenwolf.
A neighborhood staple for decades. Predictably excellent. The penne with marinara and goat cheese is incredibly simple, yet one of the best pasta dishes I've had anywhere.
Delicious food. Great specials. Great desserts. Great service. Don’t sleep on this neighborhood gem.
It's good, but it's not the outstanding fine dining experience I remember from 20 years ago.

I've always been in love with this place. We went night before our half marathon and it was so freakin delicious!!! WE are a huge fan of their ravioli - they have all kinds and its to die for good. Their risotto is also so yummy. Ten times better than an olive garden etc...
This place is such a gem! The butter and sage ravioli was incredible and clearly handmade. Get the meatball appetizer! Service was excellent - everyone’s so friendly.
It was some of the best Italian food I have ever had. Everything was absolutely fantastic!
Solid Italian food often.
Excellent, authentic, Italian food. On our list of favorite places.
Great brunch food.
Good food, great and consistent service
Food was excellent.... once we got it.  Had to wait 45 minutes to get our entrees.
It was good but everyone got heartburn
Generic average Italian fare.
Friendly service!
Have lived across the street for more than a year and only now trying this place for the first time. Huge mistake. New favorite Rigatoni.

Vinci has been providing consistently great food for decades, an important point for the many people--like us--who have pre/post Steppenwolf Theater dinner here. The portions are substantial, well-priced, and full of flavor. Pork chops are a favorite as is the seafood linguine. The ravioli pasta dish was delicious and substantial. Beware: pace yourself! It's hard to resist the complimentary bread. And, save room for the desserts, though I had to skip the Tiramasu this time. Staff and service are incredible. From the time you enter the place until you leave, you are a special guest, no matter how busy they get. And, the kitchen staff deserves kudos for providing so many fabulous meals to a full house geared up for theater. Don't even think about coming here without a reservation!
Excellent food
Great food
Food and service excellent.  Was after play at Royal George theater right down the street.
Bartender was great! Food was really good

Kind of a last minute decision to come here on NYE, but I'm really glad we did. The food was amazing and the servers were all very friendly and attentive. They do a good job giving it a rustic atmosphere inside. Definitely planning on coming back.
Venerable pre-theater dinner spot on Halsted. Always a solid experience.
Delicious Italian. The chicken was incredibly delicious
Fun, cozy, accommodating.
The service and the food is excellent!

Vinci is a tired old restaurant that would probably not be in business anymore if not for its close proximity to two big theaters, and the paucity of other options in the neighborhood. If you like big portions and a big bread basket, you might love this place. Pastas and entrees are hit-or-miss.
Excellent home-style Italian food
Had a great experience. The food was perfectly prepared. There is comfortable atmosphere.
Great flavors and sights, very nice staff.
Really good food. Very attentive service. Classic Italian.
Great service! Dessert was delicious !
Delicious Italian food in a lovely setting. Locals hang out at the front bar. Empties out fairly early in the evening.
Our "go to" restaurant before the theater at Steppenwolf. Also love their monthly wine tasting dinners. Excellent food and service.
Great food and staff. My parents and nephew eat here weekly

Went there for brunch, sat outside with our dog. The bottomless mimosas are a great deal! The food was ok, but what really makes this place great is the service. I was taking my last sip of my drink when the waiter was putting another one down. Make sure to get the bread, they make their brioche in house every day and it’s soft and delicious.
Excellent for brunch and dinner.
I had the best pork chop I have ever had in my life.
A mid level italian restaurant with average prices and respectable food. Close to Steppenwolf
Wonderful Space, great waitstaff, fabulous food and drinks.
Great Italian food

It might seem like the perfect place to eat before/after a show at Steppenwolf. And it is. The food is terrific, traditional italian and the service is pretty good. The only problem is that everyone you're seeing the show with had the exact same idea and they'll all there either before the show; telling the staff, "Can you hurry up, we have to make a show." The other half comes in after and pretend they know of anything about theatre criticism.
Very good food
One of the only Italian Restaurants who have a wine dinner every month on the 2nd Wedsday of every month Fabulous foods and wine every month.!
Great food, inovative chef. Good service.
Always a favorite for delicious food, great drinks, excellent​ wines, friendly and knowledgeable staff, a relaxing atmosphere and reasonable prices.  It feels like going home every time I'm there.

We just had the most wonderful lunch experience at Vinci Restaurant with a friend and was so happy to find this restaurant.  All of the food was very tasty and the service was the best. The wait staff was a delight to talk with and so attentive to us. The prices were extremely reasonable, also. We will definitely return!
Food and service very good.
Wait staff was a bit in attentive at times (walked by several times without collecting check, seemed impatient, etc) but seemed apologetic. Food was very good.
Excellent service and fine Italian food. Great place for before or after theater.
Had a great experience.  Can't remember the name of the pasta, butt it was veal. It was the best! The Creme Brule wad perfectly prepared.   Comfortable atmosphere.
Very good food, tiramisu made me feel, I'm in Italy. Service was excellent. Definitely will come again!
Leaning towards the pricy end, considering the simple (PS: a sunset is simple, so, context) menu and atmosphere but it's well worth it!
Good food, good services, price is ok (because of the location). Atmosphere is great. Good place for couple to dine in.
Delicious food with simple ingredients. Grilled octopus, eggplant and ravioli were all fantastic. Good service, good wine list and a nice lively bar
We hosted a birthday party here and the staff was fantastic.
High quality rustic Italian restaurant.

Delicious drinks (cocktails and wine) and food (my seafood pasta was excellent), and a nice, peaceful, somewhat "homey" dining atmosphere. It turned out getting a liiiittle pricey once everything was said and done, but not too bad, and was a nice stop before heading over to Steppenwolf for a show (I hate to lump them in with the theater, because they're their own thing, but it's also why I know about them).
Great authentic Italian food with good prices!
A favorite after or before Steppenwolf. Very good food with excellent service and a nice place.
Consistently good food and service. If possible ask to sit in the back room. It's a bit nicer ambiance.
Classic local Italian place for the theater set.
I was surprised at how yummy the food was in this tucked away place on Halsted. The staff was uniformly friendly and charming, the food was prepared with real care. Don't miss the polenta.
Great garlic spread for the bread, especially dipped in mussels

I have been coming to this restaurant for over 15 years. Try the wine dinners held on the second Wednesday of every month. Great staff, delicious food and a fantastic wine list. I try not to order the same thing. So, I love the specials. You don't have to spend a lot of money for a great meal. We go for special occasions, brunch. Or drop by for a couple drinks. Highly recommended if you are going to one of the theaters in the area.
Best bartenders. Very friendly staff and great food. Good wine selection as well!
Great Italian food with very attentive service. We went on a night at primetime, however, there was no wait.

The food was really good, but I felt the decor was a little over the top, and the space was not that comfortable. I was somehow too hot and too cold at the same time. The restaurant was also huge and kind of confusing, so not very intimate. The food was really good, though.

Yum! First time coming. Say outside because it was beautiful out. They being fresh bread to the table. You have to ask for olive oil which is weird and that comes on a plate. No biggie though but weird.  Ordered caprese salad to start and share with my friend. It was delicious. Very fresh. It was a mix of olive oil and balsamic. Perfect flavoring.  Wanted to try something different. I got Hand-made Fazzoletto which I never heard of. Hand-made Fazzoletto with mussels, shrimp, calamari, octopus, zucchini, tomato pesto sauce. YUM!! It was so interesting but delicious. It had pasta on the bottom that looked like a sheet. Then the toppings inside. Then another sheet of pasta on the top. The pasta was good and the seafood was perfectly cooked. I think I would have likes it even more with a white sauce instead. The red sauce wasn't amazing. Kind of overpowering.

My wife took me here for my birthday recently and all I can say is ‘wow’! There was not one aspect of my experience that I did not enjoy.  Walking into the restaurant, the ambiance was dimly lit, noise level ideal, and décor exquisitely crafted to provide an authentic Italian feel.  The wait staff was extremely knowledge about the menu, as they described the dishes in superb detail we had question on. They were also attentive, cleaning off dishes promptly, and ensuring your glass was never more than half empty. Each dish we had, from antipasti to dessert, was outstanding. I highly recommend the Roasted Eggplant to start, and the Grilled Beef Tenderloin for an entrée. Overall, a top-notch restaurant to which I will definitely return.
went for a dinner date with my husband , very average food but great decor. felt like i was in Italy. Service was slow. Would not go again.

I ate here for the first time on my birthday last week specifically because they had a gluten-free menu. It was great! Our server was really accommodating when what my Mom wanted wasn't exactly on the menu. We actually sat outside and it was just perfect!  PS, the bartender was awesome! Super friendly guy to talk to while I was waiting for my family to show up.
Always a great meal...and they accommodate diners with gluten-free restrictions. Always the best risotto in town and attentive service.
Had their seafood stuffed ravioli.
